NNAAMMEE
       df - disk free

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ddff [ --ii ] [ filesystem ... ] [ file ... ]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _D_f  prints out the amount of free disk space available on the specified
       _f_i_l_e_s_y_s_t_e_m_, e.g.	``/dev/rp0a'', or on the filesystem in which the spec-
       ified  _f_i_l_e_, e.g. ``$HOME'', is contained.  If no file system is	speci-
       fied, the free space on all of the normally  mounted  file  systems  is
       printed.	 The reported numbers are in kilobytes.

       Other options are:

       --ii     Report also the number of	inodes which are used and free.

FFIILLEESS
       /etc/fstab     list of normally mounted filesystems

